    {
      "question": "An architect is designing a storage tank whose volume $V(x)$ is represented by a cubic polynomial $V(x) = 2x^3 + 3x^2 - 8x + 3$. The dimensions of the base are related to a linear factor of this polynomial. A safety regulation requires that the polynomial be verified using the division algorithm to ensure stability under different pressure conditions represented by a divisor $g(x) = x - 1$.",
      "type": "case_study",
      "marks": 4,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "i",
          "type": "mcq",
          "question": "What is the remainder when $V(x)$ is divided by $(x - 1)$?",
          "answer": "(A)",
          "options": [
            "(A) $0$",
            "(B) $1$",
            "(C) $-1$",
            "(D) $2$"
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "ii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Find the quotient when $V(x)$ is divided by $(x - 1)$.",
          "answer": "$2x^2 + 5x - 3$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Use synthetic division or long division.",
              "Divide $2x^3$ by $x$ to get $2x^2$.",
              "Subtract $(2x^3 - 2x^2)$ from $V(x)$ to get $5x^2 - 8x + 3$.",
              "Divide $5x^2$ by $x$ to get $5x$.",
              "Subtract $(5x^2 - 5x)$ to get $-3x + 3$.",
              "Divide $-3x$ by $x$ to get $-3$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$(2x^3 + 3x^2 - 8x + 3) = (x - 1)(2x^2 + 5x - 3)$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iii",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "Factorize the quadratic quotient obtained in the previous step.",
          "answer": "$(2x - 1)(x + 3)$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Split the middle term for $2x^2 + 5x - 3$.",
              "$2x^2 + 6x - x - 3$",
              "$2x(x + 3) - 1(x + 3)$"
            ],
            "derivation": "$(2x - 1)(x + 3)$"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "iv",
          "type": "vsa",
          "question": "State the three zeros of the polynomial $V(x)$.",
          "answer": "$1, 1/2, -3$",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "The zeros are $x=1$ (from the divisor) and the roots of $(2x-1)(x+3)=0$."
            ],
            "derivation": "$x = 1, x = 1/2, x = -3$"
          }
        }
      ],
